Description of female. Mean body length (excluding caudal setae) 1,155 µm (
1,150 –1,160 µm
) and mean body width 719 µm ( 717–721 µm ) ( n =2). Body ( Fig. 1A ) with prossomal shield flattened, well-sclerotized, showing radiation bands along outer margin. Pedigerous somites 2–4 free. Pedigerous somite 4 expanded, covering urosome except the tip of caudal rami.
